      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. So if the environment is basically this tiny, invisible battlefield of microbes, is there something that can trigger a sudden shift? Like, what would cause the balance to swing so wildly from one day to the next? Is it just the nutrients, or is there some other factor in the chemistry that makes them stop working suddenly?",
